      "writtenOn": "2018-09-13T01:08:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think we should store this paint by reference here. It should work out fine in the current code but its not obvious. The paint is updated each time before the cache is used, and that use happens to be scoped within the paint\u0027s lifetime.\n\nCould we just have all methods which lazily create the context have the paint or effects passed in? So this class doesn\u0027t need to keep a reference to it.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 699,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 699,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "cbe7ee6eb844fae806b2029a2856480dace596d3",
